  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Regarding `TARGET_COMMITTEE_SIZE`, the spec currently has a note as follows,\r\n\r\n> For the safety of crosslinks a minimum committee size of 111 is recommended...  The shuffling algorithm generally ensures (assuming sufficient validators) committee sizes at least `TARGET_COMMITTEE_SIZE // 2`.\r\n\r\nThe second part seems incorrect: `get_new_shuffling()` produces committees of size at least `TARGET_COMMITTEE_SIZE` (not divided by two).\r\n\r\nThe current value for `TARGET_COMMITTEE_SIZE ` is 256. In view of the first part of the comment, ought it be 128?",
